  "title": "Automotive Mechanic",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will perform maintenance servicing and repairs on motor vehicles, conduct diagnostic checks and troubleshooting, and carry out engine and automatic transmission overhauls to ensure vehicle safety and performance.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform maintenance servicing and repair tasks on motor vehicles to ensure operational reliability</li><li>Conduct diagnostic checks and troubleshoot vehicle systems to identify and resolve mechanical issues</li><li>Overhaul engines and automatic transmissions to restore vehicle functionality and performance</li><li>Conduct quality checks and road tests to verify repair effectiveness and vehicle safety</li><li>Communicate effectively with Service Advisors regarding service and repair status and requirements</li><li>Support customer service operations and workshop activities to maintain smooth workflow</li><li>Maintain workshop facilities, tools, and equipment to ensure a safe and efficient working environment</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the Workshop Manager to support workshop operations</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in vehicle mechanics with skills in diagnostics, engine repair, and transmission work</li><li>Ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team</li><li>Demonstrated responsibility, attention to detail, and adherence to safety standards</li></ul>",
